This paper is about denoising neural machine translation (NMT) training, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of trusted data and online data selection, which are common techniques in ML and data science, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses NMT, which involves deep learning and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of image data for evaluation, which could suggest a connection to computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
